  m_text: "1. Create Strong, Unique Passwords: Use long passwords with a mix of uppercase
    and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols. Avoid common words and personal
    details. \r\n\r\n2. Adopt the Passphrase Approach: Instead of random characters,
    use a series of unrelated words to form a memorable and secure passphrase. \r\n\r\n3.
    Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA): Add an extra layer of security by requiring
    a second form of verification (like a code or fingerprint) along with your password.
    \r\n\r\n4. Recognize and Prevent Attacks: Be aware of phishing scams, brute-force
    attacks, and other social engineering tactics. Never share your passwords or
    click on suspicious links. \r\n\r\n5. Utilize a Password Manager: Keep your passwords
    safe and organized by using a password manager to store unique passwords for
    every account. \r\n\r\n6. Stay Informed and Vigilant: Always update your passwords
    regularly and use secure, official channels when accessing sensitive services. "
