  m_text: "\u2022 Instead of using a complex string of random characters, create
    a memorable phrase known as a \u201CPassphrase.\u201D This method involves using
    a sequence of unrelated words to construct a strong password. \r\n\r\n\u2022
    Choose 4 to 7 unrelated words that make it harder for someone to guess. \r\n\r\n\u2022
    Adding more words to your passphrase increases its length and security significantly.
    For example, \"HorsePurpleHatRunBay\" is stronger than \"HorsePurpleHatRun.\" 
    \r\n\r\n\u2022 To easily memorize your passphrase, use a phrase that you frequently
    say or one that relates to the website you are securing. Be sure to include a
    combination of uppercase and lowercase letters, as well as symbols. \r\n\r\n\u2022
    Consider a poem that you remember well. By substituting a few letters with numbers
    and symbols, you can create a robust password. "
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 9a333f184b96ee0448e37a1d2304071f, type: 2}
