  m_text: "\u2022 Always enable MFA whenever available for online accounts. This
    adds an extra layer of security to protect your information.    \r\n\r\n\u2022
    Multifactor Authentication (MFA) is a method to confirm your identity. It requires
    a second credential called a second \" factor\"\u2014to\" prove who you are.
    Eg., a code from an app or a fingerprint  \r\n\r\n\u2022 The second factor of
    authentication generally falls into one of three categories: Something you know
    (e.g., a personal identification number), something you have (e.g., a smartphone),
    or something you are (e.g., fingerprint recognition). \r\n\r\n\u2022 If someone
    attempts to sign in as you and knows your username and password, they will be
    blocked when prompted for the second factor. Without your smartphone, they cannot
    access the 6-digit code required for entry. \r\n\r\n "
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 9a333f184b96ee0448e37a1d2304071f, type: 2}
